{
  "q1_accurate": [
    {"tool": "sense_graph", "query": "nomad.Server", "note": "Located nomad/server.go:116-332 (struct), NewServer at :336, and the full composed_by list of *Server-field holders — endpoint structs (nomad/acl_endpoint.go:65, nomad/node_endpoint.go:59, nomad/job_endpoint.go:50, ...), job hooks, drainerShim nomad/drainer_shims.go:14, agent.Agent command/agent/agent.go:73 — all of which I cited verbatim in Tasks 1 and 4"},
    {"tool": "sense_graph", "query": "nomad.Server (inherits edges)", "note": "Surfaced the locally-declared interfaces *Server satisfies — nomad.JobEvalDispatcher nomad/periodic.go:41, nomad.variableTimers nomad/variables_endpoint.go:39, auth.Encrypter nomad/auth/auth.go:39, config.RPCHandler client/config/config.go:83 — which became the seed list for the entire narrowed-handle audit"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "nomad.Server", "note": "retained_via_interfaces gave me the 23-row list that is the core of Task 4: drainer.NodeDrainer nomad/drainer/drainer.go:132 via RaftApplier, volumewatcher.Watcher nomad/volumewatcher/volumes_watcher.go:20 via CSIVolumeRPC, scheduler.GenericScheduler scheduler/generic_sched.go:53 via Planner, auth.Authenticator nomad/auth/auth.go:43 via Encrypter, raftutil.FSMHelper helper/raftutil/fsm.go:29 — with the carrier/chain annotation naming the concrete satisfier"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "nomad.Server (direct_callers)", "note": "Pinned the layered RPC path symbols I cited in Task 2 — rpcHandler.handleConn nomad/rpc.go:280, rpcHandler.getLeaderForRPC nomad/rpc.go:625, planner.applyPlan nomad/plan_apply.go:241, nomadSnapshot.persistClusterMetadata nomad/fsm.go:3017"},
    {"tool": "sense_status", "query": "(no args)", "note": "Gave the project fingerprint I used for Task 1's orientation: Go project, 3093 files, top namespaces nomad/structs 3082, command 2772, nomad 2595, client/allocrunner 1546, ui/app 2437"}
  ],
  "q1_wrong": [
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "nomad.Server", "note": "retained_via_interfaces asserted chain 'agent.Agent > nomad.Server' for seven client-side holders (allocrunner.allocRunner client/allocrunner/alloc_runner.go:49, allocrunner.csiHook, allocwatcher.Config/remotePrevAlloc, config.AllocRunnerConfig, config.Config, widmgr.Signer/SignerConfig). Grep proved config.Config.RPCHandler client/config/config.go:161 is assigned ONLY in tests, so in production these hold *client.Client and never the server. The response's own retained_note flags this ('which satisfier lands at runtime is unverified'), but the chain string reads as fact and would have put 7 false holders in a lifecycle audit"},
    {"tool": "sense_search", "query": "Nomad server struct that runs the cluster, construction and shutdown lifecycle", "note": "Top hit was structs.ServerMember nomad/structs/structs.go:1227 (score 1.08) — a wire type, not the server. The actual target nomad.Server never appeared; I only got there via Server.Shutdown nomad/server.go:744 ranked 4th. Had to follow up with an explicit sense_graph on nomad.Server"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "nomad.Server", "note": "completeness verdict 'partial', resolved 64 / hidden 140, and composed_by in sense_graph was truncated at 37 with omitted_edges 111 — so I could not treat either list as the exhaustive set Task 4 demanded and had to verify the count independently"}
  ],
  "q2_fallbacks": [
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "nomad.Server", "fallback": "grep", "missing": "Exhaustiveness. With completeness 'partial' (hidden 140) and composed_by truncated, I ran grep -rE '^[[:space:]]+[A-Za-z_]+[[:space:]]+\\*(nomad\\.)?Server$' over nomad/ and command/ to get the authoritative 53 direct fields. It matched Sense's list but I could not have asserted 'EVERY place' without it"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "nomad.Server", "fallback": "grep", "missing": "Runtime satisfier verification. To test the 'agent.Agent > nomad.Server' claim I grepped RPCHandler repo-wide and found all 20+ assignments are in _test.go files — Sense reported the declared containment path but not that the production assignment site does not exist"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "nomad.Server", "fallback": "read", "missing": "Captured method values as retention. Nothing in composed_by or retained_via_interfaces showed StateFn: s.State / GetLeaderACLFn: s.getLeaderAcl at nomad/server.go:476-478 landing in Authenticator.getState/getLeaderACL nomad/auth/auth.go:52-53, nor apply: s.raftApply at nomad/server.go:1161 landing in deploymentWatcherRaftShim.apply. I found all four by reading NewServer and setupDeploymentWatcher; these ended up being the highest-risk routes in the whole audit (Tier 0)"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "nomad.Server", "fallback": "read", "missing": "Assignment/binding sites. retained_via_interfaces gave me the holder field but never the line where the value is bound, so for every one of the 20 routes in Task 5 I opened the constructor to get the pair — e.g. nomad/deploymentwatcher/deployments_watcher.go:111-113, nomad/drainer/drainer.go:177, nomad/volumewatcher/volume_watcher.go:63, nomad/auth/auth.go:82-86"},
    {"tool": "sense_graph", "query": "nomad.Server (inherits)", "fallback": "grep", "missing": "Empty-interface degeneracy. Sense listed DeploymentRPC/JobRPC as interfaces but not that they are `type DeploymentRPC interface{}` at nomad/deploymentwatcher/multiregion_ce.go:13-14 on the CE build tag — I found that with a targeted grep, and it changed the finding from 'narrowed handle' to 'full *Server behind a zero-method interface'"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "nomad.Server", "fallback": "read", "missing": "Per-child propagation. The list gave volumewatcher.Watcher and volumeWatcher as two rows but not that the child copies parent.rpc at nomad/volumewatcher/volume_watcher.go:63, nor that deploymentWatcher gets the parent passed as itself at nomad/deploymentwatcher/deployments_watcher.go:303-304 — the fan-out multiplier only came from reading the constructors"}
  ],
  "q3_hints": [
    {"tool": "sense_graph", "query_before": "sense_search 'Nomad server struct that runs the cluster, construction and shutdown lifecycle' returned structs.ServerMember as top hit", "query_after": "sense_graph symbol=nomad.Server file=nomad/server.go", "hint": "The search result row 'nomad.Server.Shutdown, nomad/server.go:744' plus next_steps suggesting sense_graph on a strong match told me the concept search had missed the type and I should name the symbol directly with a file disambiguator"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query_before": "trusted retained_via_interfaces rows as production holders", "query_after": "grep -rn RPCHandler across the repo to check whether client/config/config.go:161 is ever assigned outside tests", "hint": "retained_note: 'Which satisfier lands at runtime is unverified' — this single sentence is why I checked instead of shipping 7 false holders into a lifecycle audit"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query_before": "planned to rely on composed_by + retained_via_interfaces as the complete holder set", "query_after": "ran an explicit grep for *Server-typed struct fields to establish the true count of 53", "hint": "completeness: {verdict: 'partial', resolved: 64, hidden: 140, advice: 'Partial: total_affected is the true count. Narrow with a direction or query a specific name for the rest.'} plus 'truncated: true, omitted_edges: 111' on the sense_graph call"}
  ],
  "q4_value": "retained_via_interfaces on sense_blast. It handed me, in one call, holders whose files never import the nomad package and never name Server — drainer.NodeDrainer nomad/drainer/drainer.go:132 behind RaftApplier, volumewatcher.Watcher nomad/volumewatcher/volumes_watcher.go:20 behind CSIVolumeRPC, the three schedulers behind sstructs.Planner, auth.Authenticator behind a one-method Encrypter — complete with the carrier that satisfies each interface. That is precisely the 'easy-to-miss' class the ticket asked for, and there is no grep for it: you cannot search for a type name that the holder deliberately never mentions. Recovering that set by hand would have meant enumerating every interface declaration in the repo and checking satisfaction by inspection.",
  "q5_improve": "Give retained_via_interfaces a binding-site field and a production/test flag per row. Every row cost me a file read to answer 'where is this actually assigned, and does that assignment exist outside tests?' — the two facts the audit turned on. Concretely: config.Config client/config/config.go:88 via RPCHandler should have carried assigned_at: ['client/client_test.go:209', ...] / production_bindings: 0, which would have marked it test-only on sight; and drainer.NodeDrainer should have carried assigned_at: 'nomad/drainer/drainer.go:177', supplied_at: 'nomad/server.go:1192'. Second, treat a captured bound method value (StateFn: s.State at nomad/server.go:476) as a retention edge — those four closures were the highest-risk holders I found and Sense showed none of them.",
  "score": 8,
  "score_rationale": "retained_via_interfaces surfaced a class of holder that grep structurally cannot find — files that never name the server type (Q1, Q4) — but the audit's exhaustiveness claim, the four closure-based Tier-0 routes, the CE empty-interface degeneracy, and every binding site in Task 5 all required grep/read fallbacks (Q2), and one whole family of rows was a runtime-unverified over-approximation I had to disprove (Q1 wrong)."
}

